<plot>As originally released, this started off with 'Kay Kyser' (qv) and His Kollege of Musical Knowledge with a musical version of 'Playmates'; this was followed by 'Judy Garland' (qv) singing 'If I Forget You'; 'Bette Davis' (qv) finished up with a plea to the audience to give their nickels and dimes on behalf of the Will Rogers Memorial Commission. Presently, only three minutes of the Garland footage seems to have survived on Turner Classic Movies.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?256564</url></doc>
